I am also interested in the same issue due to kaggle data science bowl, and I have tried to subclass csviter but I don't think it is written for that purpose:
class CSVIterAug(mx.io.CSVIter):
    def Next(self):
        super().Next()
the error is: TypeError: function() argument 1 must be code, not str
I can make it compile by doing:
class CSVIterAug(mx.io.CSVIter(data_csv="./local_train-data.csv", data_shape=(30, 64, 64), label_csv="./local_train.csv", label_shape=(600,), batch_size=32)):

This  just does not complain but stil cannot able to call Next inside subclass.
Also inside src/io/iter_csv.cc, CSVIter has private members instead of protected which makes it difficult subclass it. Please let me know if subclassing possible but it seems needs a fix.
Thanks

@Gelu74 gave you all the rules we have. Actually it is mostly about coding style.

We don't have other specific rules. You can contribute just as other open-source projects.

My only suggestions are as follow:

(1) If you are fixing issues, just send the PR;

(2) When adding new features, please open an issue first. People can have discussions.
